svg.text: My career path started with back-end Django development hoping it would offer me more powerful programming skills. A month later, I enrolled in a "Deep learning and computer vision" course that gave me a sense of how AI and ML work. Yet It didn't take long 'till I figured computer vision wasn't my thing. I'm more of a practical-hands-on kind of person with LOTS of extra energy and hard work to bring in anything I engage. My need for communication has driven me slowly to prefer teamwork to individual jobs such as programming.
